g-employees-to-use-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edevelop%20new%20skill%20sets%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20continuing%20to%20deliver%20on%20their%20existing%20responsibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEY's%20findings%20were%20reported%20in%20the%20latest%20edition%20of%20the%20Big%20Four%20firm's%20Work%20Reimagined%20Survey%2C%20an%20annual%20report%20exploring%20the%20changing%20workplace%2C%20published%20earlier%20in%20November.%20The%20report%20is%20based%20on%20responses%20from%2015%2C000%20employees%20and%201%2C500%20employers%20across%2029%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerception%20is%20not%20a%20wholly%20accurate%20measure%20of%20reality%2C%20but%20employee%20workloads%20could%20be%20rising%20globally%2C%20Billeter%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEconomic%20pressures%20will%20likely%20be%20driving%20a%20'do%20more%20with%20less'%20mindset%2C%20meaning%20fewer%20people%20are%20handling%20more%20tasks.%20Role%20complexity%20is%20growing%20as%20organizations%20shift%20to%20skill-based%20models%2C%20requiring%20employees%20to%20learn%20continuously%20while%20managing%20existing%20responsibilities%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20AI%20front%2C%20poor%20integration%20and%20limited%20training%20may%20create%20temporary%20spikes%20in%20workload%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Business%20Insider%20recently%20reported%2C%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkslop-oozing-americas-white-collar-offices-generative-ai-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUS%20workers%20have%20been%20voicing%20frustration%20%3C%2Fa%3Eover%20the%20growing%20flood%20of%20AI-generated%20junk%20cluttering%20their%20workflows%20%E2%80%94%20dubbed%20workslop.%20AI%20workslop%20may%20look%20well-organized%2C%20informative%2C%20and%20professional%2C%20but%20lacks%20substance%2C%20leaving%20whoever%20receives%20it%20with%20more%20work%20sifting%20through%20the%20'slop.'%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cb172fa6-992f-40